The paper deals with a game-theoretic approach to wireless communication, specifically in the context of spectrum management. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of partial information and channel conditions, which are relevant to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions throughput and spectrum utilization, which are relevant to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT, followed by cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, and cs.MM.
